        " «مَا لَمْ يَصُفَّ فَكُلْهُ وَ مَا كَانَ يَصُفُّ فَخَلِّ سَبِيلَهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2382 - Al-Hasan ibn al-Sayqal asked Imam (as) about the chickens and birds of Mecca.\nImam (as) said: \"What does not glide (in flight), you may eat it, and what glides, let it go.\""
        ]
